This centre of outdoor activities in the middle of the village, was given by{Mr.W.G. Foster}in 1922 and had facilities for{bowls, putting, and {tennis}. When his son became 21 Mr. Foster added ornamental gates and boundary railings. Villagers provided seats and trees and plaques indicating the donor's name.{Denholme Brass Band} frequently performed in the bandstand.
The park is now used for bowls and football. It also has a{war memorial} grass for games, shrubberies,{a {childrens' playground}and{a BMX track}
{Kimberley says }When I go to the park I sometimes take my BMX bike on the BMX track. When I've had enough I go on the swings and the gypsy caravan slide.
